      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="brain" size={22} /></div><strong>Adenosine Interaction</strong><p>Valerian compounds interact with adenosine receptors — the same system that caffeine blocks. Adenosine accumulates during waking hours and promotes sleep pressure. Valerian may enhance adenosine signaling, supporting the natural drive to sleep.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="leaf" size={22} /></div><strong>No Dependency Risk</strong><p>Unlike benzodiazepines and Z-drugs, valerian does not appear to cause dependency, tolerance, or withdrawal symptoms. This makes it suitable for nightly use without the concerns associated with prescription sleep medications.</p></div>
      <div class="info-card"><div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="clock" size={22} /></div><strong>Gradual Onset</strong><p>Valerian works gradually — mild sedation within 30-60 minutes acutely, with optimal benefits after 2-4 weeks of nightly use. This makes it ideal for people seeking gentle, sustainable sleep support rather than a knockout effect.</p></div>
    </div>

